    %h1.content-head.is-center The Goal
  .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-5
  .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-3-5
    %p Software engineering (as matter of fact, most engineering fields) exhibits a notoriously low female engineer ratio. FED <i class="fa fa-code"></i> UP (Female Engineer Disparities) is a portal to present to you the first hand, unaltered results from statistics submitted by users just like you regarding female disparities in software engineering.
    %p
      %a{:href => "companies/new"} Help us
      %span increase awareness regarding the important topic of gender inequality by contributing your company's female/male software engineering ratio today! With your help, we can make this website the first open source and unbiased database for female and male software engineering statistics.
    %p
      %span You can read more about the background of this project in my
      %a{:href => "https://medium.com/@annawu/celebrating-international-woman-s-day-9ddb5def4066", target: "_blank"} Medium article.
  .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-5

  .pure-u-1
    %h1.content-head.is-center The Inspiration
  .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-5
  .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-3-5
    %p
      %span This project is inspired by Tracy Chou's
      %span
        %a{title: "Gihub repo project", href: "https://github.com/triketora/women-in-software-eng", target: "_blank"}
          Gihub repo project
      %span that she actively maintains. The initial 187 records found on FED <i class="fa fa-code"></i> UP are extracted from the text file that people have contributed to the public repo.
  .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-5

